  "hashAlgorithm": "blake2b-256",
  "body": {
    "summary": "We consider this governance action to be constitutional.",
    "rationaleStatement": "This proposal satisfies the formal requirements for governance actions set forth in Article II, Section 6 (Governance Action Standards) of the Cardano Constitution, and is presented via an immutable off-chain document (IPFS). Furthermore, the proposal is submitted under Article II, Section 7 (Treasury Withdrawal Action Standards) and specifies the purpose of the funds, the implementation period, the breakdown of costs, and the conditions for returning unused funds. Based on these points, no clear conflict with the Constitution has been identified. Accordingly, this proposal is considered constitutional. However, the proposal includes a contingency allocation to account for potential price fluctuations. Appropriate transparency in its implementation and reporting will therefore be important.",
    "precedentDiscussion": "None",
    "counterargumentDiscussion": "None",
    "conclusion": "For the reasons stated above, we determine that it is constitutional.",
